We are shooting a funeral scene and would need some extras. It is unpaid but will be credited and great experience for anyone wanting to build themselves as an actor or for a reel. We are needing people over the age of 18. 

 

The Date is 30th october 2025

The scene is a funeral so black tie and funeral attire is needed no brand names just plain black and tie wear.

The starting time is 10am finishing time is 5pm (this is the official time but we are planning to finish much earlier). Please bring some food with you as there will be a lunch break. 

Anyone arriving in a car will be able to park in the other car park next to the church.

The details of the church - address for the church is Our Lady Queen of Martys Stonebridge Lane Croxteth L11 9AZ

Please arrive on time and again thank you so much for all your help it is much appreciated. 

Details of the scene will be told on the day.

We are needing up to 20 people feel free to get in touch if you can make it

topComments.text: Why would an extra want to work for free, extra work does not lead to anything else. You wouldnt ask any other profession to work for free.

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

We want YOU to star in our commercial! 

Dreamotion Studios ¬Æ is filming an exciting commercial on Wednesday, October 22 in the beautiful Bay Theatre on Main Street in Seal Beach‚Ä¶ and we want valuable acting community members like you to be a part of it!

We have a few different time slots available if you would like to participate as a theatre audience member in the commercial:

2:00 pm - 6:30 pm

3:30 pm - 6:30 pm

5:30 pm - 9:30 pm

If you are interested and available, please fill out and submit this Google Form. 

https://forms.gle/2kvEJys6mDaCc9h37

Please also feel free to share this form with any other acting peers, friends, family, or loved ones you think may also be interested in participating. The more the merrier and all are welcome!

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the producer Baylee Corona via email at [baylee@dreamotionstudios.com](mailto:baylee@dreamotionstudios.com) or via text/call at (949) 290-0053. 

Come make Seal Beach Bay Theatre history with us and take part in this exciting production. Thank you so much!

items.text:
üé•** PAID CASTING CALL**

We are casting several roles for a series of short narrative pieces that highlight the stories of real families supported by our organization. These stories portray authenticity, warmth, and emotional depth.

**Location:** East Vancouver
**Audition Date:** October 20th

**Shooting Date:** October 23rd; must be available from 10-4 (you will not be needed the entire day)
**Compensation:** $200

**We are looking for actresses/actors to play: **

**Bruna**
* Female, late 20s to mid-40s
* Mother; caring and loving. Must convey determination, worry, and hope while navigating financial and emotional challenges for her children.

**Aisha**
* Female, early 30s to mid-40s
* Mother; warm, exhausted, and hopeful. Portrays a single parent managing multiple responsibilities with love and perseverance.

**Steven**
* Male, early 30s to mid-50s
* Father; provides care and guidance amid family hardship. Able to convey emotional strength and compassion.

**David**
* Male, mid-30s to 50s
* Father; supportive, patient, and empathetic. Represents the emotional toll of parenting through challenges while remaining steadfast for his family.

Please send a brief introduction and your headshot to **communications@ldsociety.ca. **We encourage applicants of all ethnicities and gender identities to apply.

Following auditions, we will confirm if you got the role and your timeslot via email on Tuesday, October 21st.

items.text:
üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

Project Title: A quiet Reckoning 

Type: Independent Short Film (Drama)

Production Dates: October 31st - 2nd November 

Location: Denver, CO

Compensation: $1000 Total + IMDb Credit + Footage for Reel

SYNOPSIS

Years after drifting apart, three former friends reunite to settle the affairs of someone they once loved. As they revisit the spaces and silences of their shared past, unresolved truths resurface testing the limits of forgiveness, love, and memory.

ROLES NEEDED

LEAD ROLES

AMARA (Female, 18‚Äì23, Any Ethnicity)

Ambitious and self-assured, but emotionally guarded. Her need for control hides years of guilt and suppressed grief.

JAYDEN (Male, 19‚Äì24, Any Ethnicity)

Quiet, analytical, and deeply empathetic. Carries the weight of old mistakes and longs to repair what time has broken.

TARA (Female, 18‚Äì22, Any Ethnicity)

Creative, impulsive, and raw. Her vulnerability cuts through pretense, forcing others to face what they‚Äôve avoided.

SUPPORTING ROLES

MARCUS (Male, 20‚Äì25, Any Ethnicity)

A longtime confidant  patient but emotionally spent. His honesty becomes the catalyst for long-awaited truth.

MRS. LEE (Female, 50s‚Äì60s, Any Ethnicity)

Graceful, perceptive, and quietly powerful. Offers the wisdom of perspective  reminding the young that healing is never linear.

TO SUBMIT

Please email the following to bernardfilmcastings@gmail.com

items.text:
‚Ä¢CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM 
Project Title: Before We Break
Production Type: Independent Feature Film
Shoot Date: November 1st & 2nd
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $500/day (2 days) + Reel + IMDb Credit

SYNOPSIS:
A week before their high school‚Äôs final closure, five former classmates reunite to bury a time capsule they created years ago. What begins as a nostalgic farewell quickly spirals into a raw confrontation of the truths, betrayals, and dreams that shaped their youth and the adulthood that awaits.
NOW CASTING ‚Äì LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES:

 LEAD ROLES:

Malik (Male, 18‚Äì23)
Ambitious, witty, and fiercely protective. A natural leader haunted by a decision he made senior year that fractured the group.

Zoey (Female, 18‚Äì24)
Intelligent and emotionally layered. She‚Äôs the planner of the reunion, but secretly fears what might resurface. Carries herself with quiet authority.

Jessie (Female, 19‚Äì25)
Charming and impulsive with a magnetic presence. Struggles with stability and hides vulnerability behind a fearless exterior.

SUPPORTING ROLES:

Cam (Female, 18‚Äì23)
Reserved, observant, and deeply reflective. Once the outsider of the group, she now holds crucial pieces of the past they all want to forget.

Ms. Clarke (Female, 30s‚Äì40s)
A former teacher turned school counselor. Warm, insightful, and a mentor to many, but carries her own regrets about the group‚Äôs final year.

TO SUBMIT:
Email your headshot, resume, and city of residence to:
newdawnfilming@gmail.com

1. Have a business email not a free Gmail account

items.text:
We‚Äôre seeking talented local actors for an upcoming short film shooting mid-November in the Vancouver area.

Logline:

After her brother kills the nanny who tormented them as children, a teenage girl must cover up the crime while fractured memories of their past resurface ‚Äî forcing her to choose between protecting him or saving herself.

Production Details

 Location: Vancouver, BC

Shoot Dates: Mid-November (exact dates TBA)

 Genre: Psychological Drama / Thriller

 Non-Union / Paid

ROLES

Scarlett (16‚Äì18)

Levelheaded and fiercely protective, Scarlett has carried the burden of shielding her younger brother since childhood. Calm under pressure but weighed down by responsibility, she‚Äôll sacrifice everything to keep him safe.

Sawyer (14-15 years old)

Sensitive and unguarded, Sawyer is still haunted by the trauma of their childhood. Desperate to protect himself, he makes a choice that leads to violence and binds him to his sister‚Äôs protection.

Katherine (30s)

Outwardly polished and dependable, Katherine hides a cold, controlling nature. To the world she‚Äôs a caretaker ‚Äî but to the children, she‚Äôs a source of lasting fear and trauma.

Joan (White woman, 40s)

A sharp-eyed, restless neighbor, Joan masks her loneliness with judgment and suspicion. Always watching from the sidelines, her curiosity turns dangerous when she uncovers more than she was meant to see.

Younger Scarlett (10‚Äì12)

Mature beyond her years, Scarlett shoulders the unspoken role of protector. Cautious and observant, she looks out for her younger brother even when she longs to just be a child herself.

Younger Sawyer (8‚Äì10)

Sensitive and unguarded, Sawyer depends on his sister‚Äôs protection and struggles to make sense of the cruelty around him.

Adam (Dad, 30s‚Äì40s)

Well-meaning but distracted, Adam prioritizes work over family life, leaving his children vulnerable in his absence.

Addison (Mom, 30s‚Äì40s)

Career-focused and often absent, Addison means well but unintentionally leaves Scarlett with the burden of protecting her brother.

 To Submit:

Please send your headshot, resume, and demo reel (if available) to thethingsweburyshortfilm@gmail.com  with the subject line:

‚Äú[ROLE NAME] ‚Äì [Your Name]‚Äù

Once we‚Äôve received your email, we‚Äôll send out the audition slides and next steps.

items.text:
Hello all.

I am Adam. I‚Äôm a writer, director, and producer based in Melbourne with a passion for telling bold, emotionally layered, and visually immersive stories. Every film I‚Äôve made, from the shorts to the features, has been entirely original. I write, direct, and build from the ground up, driven by a deep need to create work that has impact, feeling, and vision.

My short film *Solus*, which I wrote, directed, produced, and self-funded, went on a big international festival run. It screened in LA (twice), Berlin, Warsaw, Louisville, Manchester, London, and Sydney, and picked up several awards including Best International Short Film, Best Oceanic Film, Best Indie Film, Best Short Film, and Best Australian Film.

Outside of film, I created and produced **Falkirk Courtyard Gigs**, a passion project that turned into something really special. These were intimate, one-night-only live music events set in backyards and hidden spaces, completely DIY. I ran everything solo: programming, logistics, production, curation. Each event sold out, with over 50 people at the first and more than 100 at the second. It was a huge undertaking and proved what‚Äôs possible with vision, grit, and the right energy.

I‚Äôve also written multiple short films, several feature scripts, directed music videos (live and conceptual), and produced across many mediums. What connects it all is a strong creative identity, a belief in the power of the script, and a hunger to build meaningful work that leaves something behind.

I‚Äôm now opening myself up to paid creative work and new collaborations. Here's what I offer:

**What I can do:**

‚Ä¢ Write original short films or features
‚Ä¢ Edit or strengthen your existing screenplay
‚Ä¢ Write or shape dialogue (this is one of my biggest strengths)
‚Ä¢ Come on board as a producer and help bring your project to life
‚Ä¢ Direct your film or visual project with clarity, purpose, and vision
‚Ä¢ Collaborate creatively ‚Äî I value real connection and shared passion

I care deeply about the work. I bring a lot of heart, intensity, and clarity to every project I step into. I will push when the story needs it, not to control the process, but to honour it. And I‚Äôm always ready to meet in the middle, to negotiate, collaborate, and build something better together. I don‚Äôt cut corners. I don‚Äôt believe in doing things halfway. I want the best for the work, and for the people making it.

I‚Äôve done my time with unpaid work. At this point, I‚Äôm looking for paid opportunities. Not out of ego, but out of self-respect and respect for the energy and experience I bring. That said, I‚Äôm always open to real conversations about scope, budget, and what we can make happen.

I‚Äôm based in Melbourne but open to working with people anywhere.

If you‚Äôre looking for a writer, producer, director, or creative collaborator, or if you're just curious to talk through an idea, reach out. Let‚Äôs connect and see where it goes.

Look forward to hearing from you.
Adam Jamsek

items.text:
WeCreate Media is seeking voice talent for its client, the State of Indiana. NOTE: This project has an *extremely fast* turnaround, so please submit at your earliest availability to be considered!

The project consists of (1) :60 video intro to a conference event for the IN Chamber of Commerce, which has undergone recent restructuring. Tonally, the piece is meant to confidently inspire, without going overboard on hype.

ROLE: Narrator
Keywords are: inspiring, professional, torch-bearing, relational.

COMPENSATION: $500 Flat-fee.

USAGE: Perpetual Internal/Web use only.

AUDITION DETAILS: Submissions must supply an audition of the attached script sides to be considered.
Submission window: 24 hours: Oct. 13th, 4:00PM - Oct. 14th, 4:00PM.
Recording: Tuesday Oct. 14th, to meet Oct. 15th project deadline. Must be available to record from home-studio.

Thank you!
#voiceactors #remotework #CastingCall #CastingCall #malevocals #rushcall
Alex Ruff
Editor / Producer
alexscottruff.com
Photo by Jacek Dylag on Usplash

Hi, We're looking for a 70+ year old to act on a live game show filmed in Liverpool on the 29th October.

We're looking for someone to play a widow in a comedy sketch. 

More details can be sent to any interested parties.

Unfortunately this is not a paid role but we can pay for expenses..

thanks

We are casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.
The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates 
Rehearsals 24th -28th November 
Playing dates 1st-23rd December 

Areas
Tour A London /Home Counties -Oxon/Herts/Berks/Bucks /Wilts 
Tour B South East/Kent/Surrey/Hamps/Sussex 
Tour C East Midlands Northants/Warwickshire 
Tour D West Midlands / Shropshire/ Herefordshire /Northwest 

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 750.00  per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required. 
MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR 

Please email details asap with pref tour including a singing reel to 
info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

items.text:
Du hast Lust auf kreative Rollen, schnelle Szenen und pointierten Humor?  

Dann k√∂nnte das hier genau dein Ding sein:

Ich starte ein neues Comedy-Projekt auf TikTok, YouTube & Co.  

Geplant sind kurze POV-Sketche, Beziehungsszenen, Alltagssatire und emotionale Mini-Dramen ‚Äì alles mit einem Augenzwinkern und klarer Rollenstruktur.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- Spa√ü an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen f√ºr verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, Aff√§re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

Was dich erwartet:

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum f√ºr eigene Ideen  

- M√∂glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren  

- Hinweis zur Verg√ºtung: Das Projekt befindet sich aktuell in der Aufbauphase und wird zun√§chst ohne feste Bezahlung umgesetzt. Ziel ist es, gemeinsam etwas Starkes aufzubauen ‚Äì mit Credits in jedem Clip und der Option auf langfristige Zusammenarbeit, sobald das Projekt w√§chst.

Interesse?  

Dann schreib mir direkt hier oder per Mail an Dennis.Laubert@Web.de.

Gerne mit kurzem Video, Link zu deinem Profil oder einfach ein paar Zeilen zu dir.

Liebe Gr√º√üe, 

Dennis Laubert

**STATISTER S√òGES TIL KORTFILM**

Vi er en gruppe p√• Masterclass - Potemkin, den jyske filmskole, som er igang med et kortfilmsprojekt, og til det s√∏ger vi 7-8 statister.

Statisterne skal bruges til en scene i parken, som baggrundsfolk og af denne grund s√∏ger vi folk af alle aldre og k√∏n.

**Praktisk info:**

Jobbet er ul√∏nnet og optagelserne vil tage sted d. 21. eller 22. oktober i Viby.

**LOGLINE:**

Kortfilmen er en symbolsk film om den unge hjemmehj√¶lper, Laura, som m√∏der en √¶ldre kvinde, der lod livets muligheder smuldre v√¶k. M√∏det bliver et spejl, der tvinger Laura til at v√¶lge, om hun selv vil tage en bid af livet - eller lade tiden g√•

Ved interesse s√• kontakt endelig vores producer, Hjalte:

**Hjalte2001@gmail.com**

# **SANTA WORK AT HERTFORDSHIRE ZOO**
## üéÖ**Be Our Santa at Hertfordshire Zoo!**üéÖ

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year as Santa Claus at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

You‚Äôll be the star of our popular Christmas event, spreading joy and cheer to families visiting the zoo. From welcoming excited children to listening to Christmas wishes, you‚Äôll create unforgettable memories in our enchanting grotto.

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)

**When You‚Äôll Work:**
* 29th & 30th November
* 6th & 7th December
* 13th & 14th December
* 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd & 24th December

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

Shifts will be approximately 8 hours per day.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* ¬£22.50 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If you‚Äôve got a hearty ‚ÄúHo Ho Ho!‚Äù and would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com**

submitting asap for:

MIAMI - MEN'S DEODORANT LINE
Shoot location: TAMPA, FL (must work as a local)
Working Days: 1 (up to 10 hrs/day + 1 lunch) 
Shoot Day: October 29  
Fitting: October 24 or 27 (tbd)
Callback: October 15 (remote)

HERO OCP ROLE | ‚ÄúEvery Man‚Äù 
The athlete that Baker encounters while running. Must have a good running gait. Must also be able to do other workout routines.
Male, non-caucasian, looks 30 years old or above. Above average physique and athletic ability. He‚Äôs not shredded, but he‚Äôs 
also not the type that only works out once a week. He cares about his body and getting exercise.

OCP Usage Fee: $3,000 guaranteed payment for OCP performance of shoot services
OCP Fitting Fee: $250 per 3 hour fitting, $85 for each additional hour, if applies.
VO / ADR Session Fee: $300 per 3hr session. Additional hours at $150 per additional hour. 
Option Term 1: Option to renew for a consecutive 1-year term for all initial usage details. Fee is +10% increase from original fee.
OCP Overtime Rate:  Hours worked beyond first 8 will be paid at time and a half for hours 9-12 in 15-minute increments.
All rates listed are -20% af

If avail, please send email to miamitalentcasting@gmail.com 
for self tape info.

items.text:
We want YOU to star in our commercial! 

Dreamotion Studios ¬Æ is filming an exciting commercial on Wednesday, October 22 in the beautiful Bay Theatre on Main Street in Seal Beach‚Ä¶ and we want valuable acting community members like you to be a part of it!

We have a few different time slots available if you would like to participate as a theatre audience member in the commercial:

2:00 pm - 6:30 pm

3:30 pm - 6:30 pm

5:30 pm - 9:30 pm

If you are interested and available, please fill out and submit this Google Form. 

https://forms.gle/2kvEJys6mDaCc9h37

Please also feel free to share this form with any other acting peers, friends, family, or loved ones you think may also be interested in participating. The more the merrier and all are welcome!

If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out to the producer Baylee Corona via email at [baylee@dreamotionstudios.com](mailto:baylee@dreamotionstudios.com) or via text/call at (949) 290-0053. 

Come make Seal Beach Bay Theatre history with us and take part in this exciting production. Thank you so much!

items.text:
üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

UPDATE: THESE ROLES HAVE BEEN FILLED!

BIRMINGHAM, ALABAMA area
FEATURE FILM
STAND-IN CASTING CALL
-----------------------------
Project: FEATURE FILM - "End The Wait"

Shoot Location: BIRMINGHAM, AL area
--MUST be able to work in the Birmingham, AL area as a LOCAL HIRE!! (Travel/Transportation/Accommodation will not be provided)

DATES NEEDED:  --Monday thru Friday--
MONDAY 10/13/25 -to- THURSDAY 11/13/25
-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. **MUST HAVE FULL OPEN AVAILABILITY EVERY DAY Monday - Friday to be able to work every week day as needed

NON-UNION
Rate of PAY:  $175.00 for up to 12 hours (may not work that many hours but you will be paid for the full day even if you get wrapped sooner than 12 hours)  Overtime after 12 hours (if applicable)
_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **STAND-INS**
[CAUCASIAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, Caucasian, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female Caucasian lead actors

[AFRICAN AMERICAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, African American, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female African American lead actors
_______________________________________________
TO SUBMIT for these roles: 
Please send us an email ASAP to - onlocationcasting1@gmail.com 
With subject line BIRMINGHAM STAND-IN
Emails must include ALL of the following:   
-First & Last Name
-Phone Number
-Email Address
-Height 
-Weight 
-Clothing and Shoe Sizes 
-Current City/State you are located in
-CONFIRM you are fully available EVERY week day from 10/13 to 11/13 in Birmingham, AL
--Please provide a resume and/or a brief description of your Stand-in experience (project, actor, length of time - please don't just say "Yes I have Standin experience")
-Recent Color Photos of you (prefer cell phone photos rather than professional headshots - NO FILTERS!) . Please include at least (2) photos - (1) Close up and (1) Full Body Standing (make sure you are the ONLY person in your photo, no sunglasses or hats)

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm working on a fun, over-the-top comic project and I‚Äôm looking for a female voice actor to bring some lines to life. It‚Äôs a silly, exaggerated parody, so feel free to get creative and go a little wild üòÖ.

The project is just for personal enjoyment and practice, so nothing will be shared publicly or sold. Your voice will just be part of this small private experiment, and it‚Äôs totally fine if you just want to have fun with it!

If you enjoy voice acting and want to join for a fun, lighthearted project, send me a short demo or DM‚ÄîI‚Äôd love to hear your take!

Dance&Arts is thrilled to be growing, and we're looking for passionate **teachers** to join our team right here in **Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young children (aged 4-16) through creative and performing arts, we want to hear from you!

 

We're seeking instructors for a variety of classes. Do you teach any of these styles?

 

‚úÖ **Dance (all styles)**

‚úÖ **Drama**

‚úÖ **Musical Theatre**

‚úÖ **Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)**

‚úÖ **Arts & Crafts**

 

**üí∞ Great Pay:** We offer **¬£30 per hour**.

 

**IMPORTANT DBS REQUIREMENT**

Applicants must have a valid **Enhanced DBS**, or must be **willing to obtain one**. If you need to apply for one, **we will happily provide you with guidelines **for the process!

 

**üì© How to Apply:** Send your valid **Enhanced DBS and CV** to **admin@dancearts-uk.com**.

 

***Crucially, please include the position you are applying for and the location in the subject line of your email (e.g., Dance Teacher - Birmingham).***

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation in Birmingham!

 

We're also seeking instructors in **London, Nottingham, and Manchester**!

Casting Call 

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-40 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 21th of October day time in Croydon, London, next to Waddon station.
If actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution. Also, after getting funding could be some early compensation by agreement.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me:
I am producer and one of the directors of the film. My name: Ieva Kondrataviciute 
 Email: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com
Contact WhatsApp: +44 7548710376 

Respectfully,

Ieva K.

topComments.text: I would be would take too long and cost too much to get to Croydon. Shame that. Looks good.

Actors (non-union) needed for a documentary regarding Elizabeth Johnson Jr who was the last convicted witch to be exonerated from the 1692 Salem Witchcraft Trials.

The ideal actor for Elizabeth will have strawberry blond or slight red hair, be of average height and able to portray early 20s.

Two additional actors will be needed as elders (40-60) who arrest her and walk her away.

The shoot will require one day in early November or early December on north of Boston. Pay will be negotiated.  Access to a late 17th century costume is a plus. Send headshot, resume and November, December availability to SalemHistoricalTours@gmail.com

items.text:
Announcing our next Demidov Acting Technique Two Day Intensive on February 14th & 15th 2026 at Pushkin House in London! 

This Two Day Intensive will introduce actors to Demidov‚Äôs unique approach to accessing our inner freedom, cultivating our intuition, perception, spontaneity, and ability to surrender fully to our inner urges and the truth of our experience in the moment. 

Over the course of this weekend, we will discover how to orient ourselves in the circumstances of a given text and to surrender to them fully. We will learn how circumstances become ‚Äògiven‚Äô, and how they become clearer and deeper every time we repeat a scene. We will learn to let ourselves be driven by the force of circumstances, rather than forcing ourselves to do, think or feel anything. In this way, living as character becomes effortless and spontaneous.

This Intensive is for actors both new to the Demidov work, and also for those who would like to go deeper into it. 

The Demidov Organic Acting Technique empowers actors to connect deeply with their unique creative individuality by guiding them to recognise and trust their innate artistic instincts. It is an approach that cultivates faith in the actors‚Äô own talent and foster spontaneous performances that emerge organically, allowing actors to consistently access inspiration and fully express their true creative potential. 

Click the link below to read more and email us at office@demidovstudiolondon.com with any questions!

https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/courses/demidov-two-day-intensive-feb26

Poster Photo  by: @kelsey_m_j 

~

Demidov Studio London

items.summary:
Announcing our next Demidov Acting Technique Two Day Intensive on February 14th & 15th 2026 at Pushkin House in London! 

This Two Day Intensive will introduce actors to Demidov‚Äôs unique approach to accessing our inner freedom, cultivating our intuition, perception, spontaneity, and ability to surrender fully to our inner urges and the truth of our experience in the moment. 

Over the course of this weekend, we will discover how to orient ourselves in the circumstances of a given text and to surrender to them fully. We will learn how circumstances become ‚Äògiven‚Äô, and how they become clearer and deeper every time we repeat a scene. We will learn to let ourselves be driven by the force of circumstances, rather than forcing ourselves to do, think or feel anything. In this way, living as character becomes effortless and spontaneous.

This Intensive is for actors both new to the Demidov work, and also for those who would like to go deeper into it. 

The Demidov Organic Acting Technique empowers actors to connect deeply with their unique creative individuality by guiding them to recognise and trust their innate artistic instincts. It is an approach that cultivates faith in the actors‚Äô own talent and foster spontaneous performances that emerge organically, allowing actors to consistently access inspiration and fully express their true creative potential. 

Click the link below to read more and email us at office@demidovstudiolondon.com with any questions!

https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/courses/demidov-two-day-intensive-feb26

Du hast Lust auf kreative Rollen, schnelle Szenen und pointierten Humor?  

Dann k√∂nnte das hier genau dein Ding sein:

Ich starte ein neues Comedy-Projekt auf TikTok, YouTube & Co.  

Geplant sind kurze POV-Sketche, Beziehungsszenen, Alltagssatire und emotionale Mini-Dramen ‚Äì alles mit einem Augenzwinkern und klarer Rollenstruktur.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- Spa√ü an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen f√ºr verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, Aff√§re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

Was dich erwartet:

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum f√ºr eigene Ideen  

- M√∂glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren  

- Hinweis zur Verg√ºtung: Das Projekt befindet sich aktuell in der Aufbauphase und wird zun√§chst ohne feste Bezahlung umgesetzt. Ziel ist es, gemeinsam etwas Starkes aufzubauen ‚Äì mit Credits in jedem Clip und der Option auf langfristige Zusammenarbeit, sobald das Projekt w√§chst.

Interesse?  

Dann schreib mir direkt hier oder per Mail an Dennis.Laubert@Web.de.

Gerne mit kurzem Video, Link zu deinem Profil oder einfach ein paar Zeilen zu dir.

Liebe Gr√º√üe, 

Dennis Laubert

items.text:
Hallo alle miteinander,

sind Hier Produzenten unter euch die nach neuen Projekten suchen, dass Sie Finanzieren m√∂chten oder kennt jemanden der dergleichen sucht?

Bitte keine Anfragen wie "ich kann dies und das machen, wenn der Film fertig ist" damit der Film fertig werden kann braucht es einen Sponsor oder einen Produzent/in.

Ja, ich wei√ü welche Interessen ein Sponsor hat, wenn er ein Projekt finanzieren will.

Problem an dem Projekt ist, dass es sich um einen Drama/Psychothriller handelt, und Sponsoren (Gro√üe Firmen, Unternehmen) au√üerhalb der Branche daran kein Interesse haben, weil diese Soziale Projekt unterst√ºtzen).

Das Bild ist eine Requisite f√ºr den Film. Welches Unternehmen will an so einem Film Beteiligt sein in dem so ein Requisit zu sehen ist‚Ä¶

**√úber das Projekt:**

- Titel des Films/Laufzeit: C!N- Ein Drama zwischen Mutter und Tochter / ca. 20min

- Genre:  Drama, Psychothriller

- Kurzbeschreibung: Ein Drama zwischen Mutter und Tochter nimmt einen dramatischen Verlauf und zwingt die Mutter zu einer schwerwiegenden Entscheidung.

Einige grobe Infos als √úberblick (Cast & Crew steht alles):

- 5 Darsteller

- 18 Crewmitglieder

- 1 Location (Dreh findet in einem Objekt statt)

- Drehtage 4-5

Alle Beteiligten unterst√ºtzen das Projekt unentgeltlich.

Die √ºbliche frage die die meisten von euch wohl kennen:

Wof√ºr Sponsor/Produzent, wenn alle unentgeltlich das Projekt unterst√ºtzen?

Diejenigen von euch aus der Branche wissen wieviel Aufwand und Kosten hinter so einem Projekt stecken.

- Unterkunft,

- Verpflegung

- Anreisekosten

- u.v.m.

Wer Interesse hat, mehr Infos ben√∂tigt oder hilfreiche Tipps hat bitte via PN melden.

 

LG
Levent Aksoy

Title: Forever Home

Genre: Horror/Thriller

Logline: A young couple tours their dream home with an unsettling real estate agent, only to discover the house holds a dark secret.

Roles:

-Raymond Russo

Age: 45-60

Gender: Male

Ethnicity: White

Description: A veteran real estate agent with a polished exterior. He is charming, articulate, and seemingly trustworthy. Beneath the polished exterior, however, is something deeply unsettling.

Requirements: Actor must be skilled with subtle menace and controlled delivery. Suited look; sharp features a plus.

-Susan

Age: 25-35

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Any

Description: An optimistic, curious young woman who‚Äôs excited about starting a new chapter with her husband. She‚Äôs practical yet impulsive when her curiosity is piqued.

Requirements: Needs range from natural warmth to terror. Must handle emotional intensity and physical acting in horror scenes.

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Paid

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email headshot, resume and demo reel to email provided (luke@lostefilms.com). We will send a copy of the script and audition instructions.

Shooting Schedule: One short shoot day must happen as soon as possible to capture the brief exterior scenes before leaves are all gone. The other full shoot day will be scheduled close to the exterior shoot day.

Filming Location: Denver metro area

Looking forward to your submissions!

CU DENVER STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Title: *Mannequins*

Genre: Thriller/Horror

Written and Directed by Archer Beck

Produced by Owen Etter

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the family‚Äôs image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellion‚Äîuntil Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly power‚Äîand must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family she‚Äôs ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Union Status: Non-Union

Production Type: Student Short Film

Runtime: 10-12 minutes

Compensation: Meals Provided, Any Transportation Fees Paid For, Film & IMDb Credit, Copy of Final Cut

Location: Denver Area

Submission Details:

To submit for audition, please send headshot(s), resum√©, and reel (if available) to owen.etter@ucdenver.edu.

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)
